## Task 1 – Introduction to Linux Shells

Most users rely on the Graphical User Interface (GUI), but nearly all tasks can be performed via the Command-Line Interface (CLI).
Shells provide enhanced features for commands, making CLI interaction more efficient and resource-friendly.
Analogy: GUI is like ordering food from a menu, while CLI is like cooking yourself in the OS “kitchen,” with the shell guiding you like a recipe.
Shell usage gives more power and control over the system.
Learning objectives:
- Interact with Linux shells.
- Use basic shell commands.
- Explore different types of shells.
- Write shell scripts.
- Prerequisite: completion of the Linux Fundamentals module.

