## Task 4 – Shell Scripting and Components

Basics
Scripts automate repetitive tasks.
- Written in .sh files, starting with shebang (#!/bin/bash).
Variables
- Store values for reuse.
- Example:
- bash
#!/bin/bash
echo "Hey, what’s your name?"
read name
echo "Welcome, $name!"
Loops
- Repeat tasks automatically.
- Example:
- bash
#!/bin/bash
for i in {1..10}
do
  echo $i
done
Conditional Statements
Execute code only if conditions are met.
- Example:
- bash
#!/bin/bash
read name
if [ "$name" == "Stewart" ]
then
  echo "Here is the secret!"
fi
Comments
Written with # to explain code.
Improve readability and maintainability.

